# Version metadata — kaptaind's own save_version rewrites VERSION + Cargo.toml
# on every auto-commit (and the test build then touches Cargo.lock). If the
# watcher sees those writes, each commit re-triggers the next cluster and the
# daemon cascades (observed: v0.1.6 -> v0.1.9 in three self-commits). These
# files are still staged in every commit via cluster meta-staging, so version
# bumps land in history; they just can no longer START a cluster. Consequence:
# a lone dependency edit to Cargo.toml/Cargo.lock will not auto-commit on its
# own — it rides along with the next source change, or commit it manually.
VERSION
Cargo.toml
Cargo.lock
